OL,3,CEngland fans remain confident despite
OL,4,C'unexciting' Panama win
OL,6,FMore than 15,000 England fans
OL,7,Ftravelled to the match against Panama,
OL,8,Fwith many once again heard booing the
OL,9,Fenforced hydration breaks in the
OL,10,Fmiddle of both halves.
OL,12,FAfter the Three Lions managed to
OL,13,Fsecure top spot in the World Cup
OL,14,Fgroup, another supporter said he is
OL,15,Fcontemplating a cheap trip to Atlanta
OL,16,Ffor the knockout stages despite
OL,17,Fjokingly saying it might lead to a
OL,18,Fdivorce.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1782616677
OL,3,CEngland fans remain confident despite
OL,4,C'unexciting' Panama win
OL,6,FJonathan Pearce, from Derby, told PA:
OL,7,F"We were looking at flights earlier
OL,8,Fand it was 40 dollars to Atlanta and
OL,9,Fthen only #300 back home so, I might
OL,10,Fget divorced but I'm on about doing it.
OL,12,F"So I'm not sure she'll be happy but
OL,13,Fthe kids will appreciate it later on `
OL,14,F'yeah, dad was a legend and he just
OL,15,Fstayed out'."
OL,17,FDespite Mr Pearce saying he found a
OL,18,Fcheaper option, other fans pointed to
OL,19,Fthe cost of following England at the
OL,20,Ftournament as to why they were not
OL,21,Fgoing to the first knockout game.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUwD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
